value.Title: Strategies For Teaching Individuals With Mild And Moderate Disabilities Primary & Elementary Grades
Psychometrics With R Program
value.Description: Class Description: Psychometrics literally means “psychological measurement.” It is the methodology that deals with designs, administrations, and interpretations of measurement on individuals’ constructs such as abilities, attitudes, personality, knowledge, quality of life, and so on. This class provides a conceptual framework of classical test theory and latent trait theory. Students will learn the techniques and methods and apply them to educational and psychological assessments. Topics that will be covered include reliability, validity, generalizability, Item Response Theory, test construction and design, Differential Item Functioning, scaling, linking, equating, and adaptive testing. R programming language will be introduced for various tasks such as point estimation and Monte Carlo simulation.
